text.tspan: 5th percentile
Based on the BRFSS, the CDC regularly warns that
a third of Americans don't sleep the recommended
seven hours a day. According to ATUS, the number
is closer to a sixth.
The median daily sleep for those who
fill out diaries is 8h:40; about 8h:00
on weekdays and 9h:00 on weekends.
When instead asked about how much
they sleep on average, the median
person reports 7h:00.
The Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System survey from Centers for
Disease Control and Prevention and the American Time Use Survey from
Bureau of Labor Statistics ask adult Americans how much they sleep.
The BRFSS asks "On average, how many hours of sleep do you get in a
24-hour period?" while ATUS has respondents fill out detailed diaries. The
two methods give very different results.
